bound, due to Ben-Or, who\nshowed that elementary symmetric polynomials can be computed by algebraic\nformula (in fact depth-$3$ formula) of size $O(n^2)$. Prior to this work,\nBen-Or's construction was known to be optimal only for algebraic formulas of\ndepth-$3$ [SW01].\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 26 Nov 2019 19:06:47 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 18 Mar 2020 16:17:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-19"}
