'reasonable implication algebras' are just one way to define a\nparaconsistent set theory. Our twist-valued models are adapted to provide a\nclass of twist-valued models for (PS3,*), thus generalizing L\\\"{o}we and\nTarafder result. It is shown that they are in fact models of ZFC (not only of\nZF).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 26 Nov 2019 21:01:27 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 1 Dec 2019 14:26:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-12-03"}
