ion of\n$a_\\perp=3.4^{+2.1}_{-1.0}$ au. The planetary system is located in the Galactic\nbulge with a line-of-sight separation from the source star of $D_{\\rm\nLS}=1.21^{+0.96}_{-0.63}$ kpc. The event shows that there are a range of\ndeviations in the signatures of host stars for apparently isolated planetary\nlensing events and that it is possible to identify a host even when a deviation\nis subtle.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 27 Nov 2019 04:55:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-02-19"}
