ze the\ncase of weight-tied autoencoders (which is a commonly used architectural choice\nin practical settings) and prove that in the over-parameterized setting,\ntraining such networks from randomly initialized points leads to certain\nunexpected degeneracies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 27 Nov 2019 06:45:36 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 2 Mar 2020 17:47:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-03"}
