 ENSO events\nbeing known to be locked to the seasonal cycle, these results should be\nextended to the non-autonomous case. More generally, the reduction approach\ntheorized in [CTND19], complemented by our understanding of the spectral\nproperties of reference systems such as the stochastic Hopf bifurcation,\nprovides a promising methodology for the analysis of low-frequency variability\nin high-dimensional stochastic systems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 27 Nov 2019 13:27:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-11-28"}
