t parameters, dMRI-based fiber tracking performance was\nsignificantly improved, while minimizing false positives and impossible\ncross-hemisphere connections. Parameters optimized for 10 tracer injection\nsites showed good generalization capability for other brain samples. These\nresults demonstrate the importance of data-driven adjustment of fiber-tracking\nalgorithms and support the validity of dMRI-based tractography, if appropriate\nadjustments are employed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 27 Nov 2019 15:22:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 24 Apr 2020 17:43:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-28"}
